data.content:
Here's the minimal program (`Program.cs`) targeting `net8.0`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
});
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}`

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`). The record declaration goes after the top-level statements (C# requirement).
